msContents.summary: Ethical excerpts from the Talmud and various midrashim.

msItem.title: Ethical excerpts from the Talmud and various midrashim.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 33; written lines: 32; Uniform layout. Visible pricking in outer margins and complete hard-point ruling. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable, Many marginal additions and notes. Initial words and titles in square characters.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi semi-cursive script of the 14th century. Berakhiah(?): marked off on folios 25r, 133r.

binding.p: BM in-house. Ivory vellum spine. Spine: 'Collectanea on Moral Precepts. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 1389.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Fischl Hirsch: purchased by the British Museum from him on 08 March 1876: inscribed (folio [166v]).
